uted definitions of poetry from the viewpoint of a practicing writer and dedicated reader, A Vertical Art makes an insightful and entertaining case for the power and potential of poetry today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh  aA Little Help.  aA Song to David.  aA. E. Housman.  aAdage.  aAllen Ginsberg.  aAnna Akhmatova.  aApathy.  aBarry Hines.  aBlank verse.  aBob and wheel.  aBook.  aCleanness.  aConceit.  aConfessional writing.  aCreative writing.  aCymbeline.  aDark Night of the Soul.  aDeath of a Naturalist.  aDiary.  aDramatic monologue.  aDream vision.  aEdgar Allan Poe.  aEdward Hirsch.  aElizabeth Bishop.  aEnglish poetry.  aErica Jong.  aErudition.  aEssay.  aExcursus.  aExtended metaphor.  aFart.  aFear of Flying (novel).  aFuck.  aGoblin Market.  aHilary Mantel.  aHow They Brought the Good News from Ghent to Aix.  aHowl and Other Poems.  aHyperbole.  aImagism.  aIn Parenthesis.  aIncorruptibility.  aJ. R. R. Tolkien.  aJargon.  aJohn Wain.  aKazuo Ishiguro.  aKenneth Koch.  aLeonard Cohen.  aLibido.  aLiterary fiction.  aLord Alfred Douglas.  aLyrical Ballads.  aMan of the People.  aMaurice Riordan.  aMelodrama.  aMutability (poem).  aNarcissism.  aNecromancy.  aOf Mice and Men.  aOrwellian.  aPararhyme.  aPen name.  aPeter Reading.  aPhilip Larkin.  aPhrenology.  aPoetic diction.  aPoetry.  aPun.  aR. S. Thomas.  aRay Bradbury.  aRhyme.  aRobert Burns.  aRobert Conquest.  aRobert Frost.  aRomanticism.  aRound Table.  aSayre's law.  aSelf-help book.  aSensationalism.  aSimile.  aSkunk Hour.  aSonnet 23.  aTed Hughes.  aThe Anthologist.  aThe Faerie Queene.  aThe Female Eunuch.  aThe Grand Budapest Hot